        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Storm Shelter Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a one-time refundable tax credit of up to $2,500 for the costs of installing a storm shelter to be used at a taxpayer's principal residence. To qualify for the credit, the residence may not be valued at more than $250,000. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
